text.paragraph:
Lamotrigine tablets are contraindicated in patients who have demonstrated hypersensitivity (e.g., rash, angioedema, acute urticaria, extensive pruritus, mucosal ulceration) to the drug or its ingredients [see Boxed Warning,
                      Warnings and Precautions (5.1, 5.2)
                     ].

list.item:
Aseptic meningitis [see Warnings and Precautions (
                         5.5)
                        ]
